Part I: Basics of Blackjack
In blackjack, the object of the game is to draw cards and end the game with a 
hand value that is higher than your opponent, without going over 21.
Players take turn drawing cards (Hit) and if they are satisfied with their
hand, they may choose to stop drawing (Stand)
J, Q and K counts as 10
A counts as either 1 or 11, depending on which is more advantageous

Example:
You: 3, 7, 9, 1
Opponent: J, 4, 2

You Win. 20 > 16
(You: 3+7+9+1=20)
(Opponent: 10+4+2=16) 


You: J, Q, 4
Opponent: 2, 9, 8

You Lose. Your Hand exceeds 21.
(You: 10+10+4=24)
(Opponent: 2+9+8=19)


