Part II: The Bound
In GoForX, the number you do not want to exceed is referred to as the "Bound". 
In Blackjack this number is always 21 but in GoForX this number is different every game.


2.1) Both players will have different bounds. The winner of GoForX is the player whose hand value has
the shortest distance to their bound.

Example:
Your Hand: 22  Bound: 24
Your Opponent: 23  Bound: 28

You Win! 1 < 5
(You: 24-21=1)
(Opponent: 28-23=5)


2.2) Players know their opponent's bound but not theirs. Both players' bounds have
a maximum difference of 3 (referred to as "Variance"). For example, if your opponent's
bound is 24, your bound could be anywhere from 21 to 27.


